			<title><![CDATA[Freelance User Experience Strategist]]></title>
			<department><![CDATA[UX]]></department>
			<team><![CDATA[]]></team>
			<url><![CDATA[http://enginedigital.theresumator.com/apply/gIACIM/Freelance-User-Experience-Strategist.html]]></url>
			<city><![CDATA[Vancouver]]></city>
			<state><![CDATA[British Columbia]]></state>
			<country><![CDATA[Canada]]></country>
			<postalcode><![CDATA[V6C1G9]]></postalcode>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>
With offices in Vancouver and New York, we&rsquo;re a team of strategists, creatives, and engineers, driven by a passion for crafting influential brand experiences that cross web, mobile, and social platforms. Based on a collective appreciation for brand strategy, user experience, design, and technology, we&rsquo;re uniquely qualified and motivated to redefine how organizations and people engage in an increasingly digital world.</p>
<p>
<strong>The Job</strong></p>
<p>
In the role of UX Strategist, you&#39;ll work within our Insight &amp; Planning team under the leadership of the Director of User Experience. You&rsquo;ll play a hands-on role defining intuitive and inspiring systems, processes, and relationships that connect people to the user experience. You will participate in the requirements definition and ideation process, helping to identify solutions that exceed the goals and objectives set by the project lead, our client partners, and their customers.</p>
<p>
In this role you will work collaboratively in the planning of creative and strategic solutions that address the complex challenges faced by brands across an increasingly fragmented digital environment. From both analytic and creative perspectives, you will take an iterative approach to planning, documentation and presentation, informed by research into user behaviors, expectation and needs, the competitive set, and market research. Throughout the process you will collaborate with a nimble team of strategists, creatives, and developers, working towards a confident presentation of insightful work.</p>
<p>
You&#39;ll participate in pitching to different audiences: agency leaders, your design and development colleagues, and client stakeholders. It&#39;s not just the creation of tight, insightful documentation that matters; you have to be able to sell the big picture as well as the detail. You will be responsible for synthesizing feedback from all of these groups into coherent UX documentation that easily tracks back to business requirements. Over the course of a project you&#39;ll eliminate the gaps and flaws in strategy, refine the design, and pursue opportunities for additional innovation, while honoring the broader context of the user experience objectives.</p>
<p>
<strong>Role &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square; ">
<li>
The ideal candidate is skilled in developing web, mobile and social experiences that meet best practices and push the boundaries of innovation</li>
<li>
Candidates should have a personal relationship and working knowledge of platforms and technologies, proving an ability to know the rules and how to break them</li>
<li>
Critical and subjective thinking, initiative to improve both product and process, along with an ability to work within a team is essential</li>
<li>
Know when and why UX deliverables such as Generative and Formative Research, User Journeys, Wireframes, Site Maps and Content Matrices are required</li>
<li>
Create and present UX deliverables within the agency and to our clients</li>
<li>
Partner with other team members to steer the user experience vision</li>
<li>
Drive principles of usability and user-centered design, and know when it&#39;s ok to cut corners</li>
<li>
Work with clients &amp; research teams to define research methodologies and participate in user testing or fieldwork as required</li>
<li>
Collaborate with cross-functional teams and our clients to ensure that the integrity of the experience is maintained at product launch and beyond</li>
<li>
Work with Client Engagement and Project Managers to ensure the momentum of projects while maintaining healthy working relationships</li>
<li>
Represent User Experience in pitch work by working with senior staff to identify opportunities that emerge during discovery, planning and scope definition</li>
<li>
Form a clear and insightful understanding of our clients&rsquo; business, their needs, and the creative opportunities and challenges that exist in their categories</li>
<li>
Work collaboratively with practice leads, senior members of the design team to generate clever, innovative, and relevant creative strategies across a broad range of media channels</li>
<li>
Balance the above with a clear appreciation for the goals and objectives of our clients, as well as those of the agency including quality and innovation, agency culture, and profitability</li>
<li>
Foster a positive team environment, mentor colleagues, and encourage the development of skills within the creative team through example, sharing and inspiration</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square; ">
<li>
Candidates should be available for meetings at the agency.</li>
<li>
BA in computer science, interaction design, cognitive science, HCI or equivalent is preferred, but equal attention given to self taught candidates with proven capabilities and experience</li>
<li>
Minimum 3-5 years experience in UX or IA creating interfaces, large scale websites, or applications</li>
<li>
Proficient with common UX principles and language including user-centered design, patterns, and design thinking</li>
<li>
Excellent knowledge of usability, accessibility and industry standards</li>
<li>
Experience with marketing-driven projects that mesh user experience with customer experience</li>
<li>
Experience working within a fast-paced team environment preferably within a creative or interactive agency setting</li>
<li>
Ability to balance user needs with business goals and technological capabilities</li>
<li>
Experience with A/B testing, web analytics, and analytics platforms</li>
<li>
Proficient using Omnigraffle, Visio, Adobe Illustrator, Keynote, and Powerpoint</li>
<li>
Familiarity with APIs, web services, and 3rd party platforms such as CMS, CRM, intranets, blog platforms, and social networks</li>
<li>
Passionate and driven about new and emerging technologies, platforms, channels, trends, and best practices</li>
<li>
Solid communication skills; ability to listen, present, and sell through ideas both internally and directly to executive level client stakeholders<br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
If this sounds like you, then we should talk.</p>
<p>
No recruiters, agencies, or phone calls please.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
